# ad/Scenario3/providers/virtualbox/Vagrantfile
#
# boxes must be at the top-level Ruby scope so the GOAD framework template
# (template/provider/virtualbox/Vagrantfile) can access it after loading this file.
#
# The Vagrant.configure block below is additive — Vagrant merges it with the
# template's own configure block. It is kept separate from the boxes definition
# to preserve the top-level scope of the boxes variable.
#
# config.ssh.insert_key = false prevents Vagrant from replacing the default
# insecure key with a per-VM generated key. All lab VMs then share the
# well-known Vagrant insecure private key, which setup_local_jumpbox.sh
# installs at ~/.vagrant.d/insecure_private_key on the jumpbox so Ansible
# can authenticate to every host with a single key path.

